You gotto set some boundaries and protocols ðŸ˜‚ Hey legally , right,  let's say you have a kid with someone and they become a shit bag absent parent. If the child is <3years old (WV) if SB absent parent go more than 48 hours without meaningful contact it can be entered as abandonment. No kidding. The court can really castrate men. Its harsh. 
 Ok so kid a little older ,(not exact now....its been a long time, some details are forgotten) ok so 9-13 Its 1 week or more of continued absence = abandonment. 
Alright,  so why let some jackass do it? You wouldnt try to swim the English channel holding onto a boat anchor would you? Set that boundary and once crossed, drop the offender like hot garbage.
Theres countless people too timid and lacking to even approach you! 1coward running away is small potatoes .
Alls fair in love and war they say. You'll only get the respect you command and some folks ain't up to the challenge. 
(Disclaimer) the ages i listed are estimated according to what I remember of west virginia law. Jesus krust the courts can be outright viscious. 
My point is,  you shouldnt be left wondering.  That's an open wound to me. Set that boundary for abandonment and stick to it. That jakaz wasnt good enough. 
"Weeks of silence"....... People experience emotion differently I guess. That sounds like torture. I say a few days with no meaningful contact = no observable relationship= grounds for immediate dismissal unless the person has been injured.  Dont squander time on scrubs! Too many new people to meet. Too much happiness out there to find.

If you get ghosted by someone it means only one thing: They didnt have the courage to directly confront you and agree to part ways. They were scared to face you.....so think of it as
